
**green gram-phaseolus mungo it is so called because of its green colour it is very commonly grown in south india but cultivated all over india generally the seeds are scattered in rice fleds after the harvest in the month of january or february the tamilians use this in food along with rice as pongal**
**சொற்குவை - அகரமுதலித் திட்ட இயக்ககம்**
- -   பாசிப் பயறு
